### 4. SVTA MOPS Update
* **Presenter:** Glenn Deen
* **Slides:** [SVTA MOPS update IETF126](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-mops-svta-mops-update-ietf126-00)

Glenn Deen provided an overview of the latest developments in the Streaming Video Technology Alliance (SVTA):
* **Open Caching:** Work continues on defining operational extensions for IETF CDNI specifications.
* **Edge Compute / QoE:** Projects are underway to standardize edge cache hosting and analytics.
* **QUIC vs. TCP Report:** The Networking and Transport group published a long-running Proof of Concept (PoC) report indicating that QUIC (HTTP/3) performance is comparable to HTTP/2 ("no worse, no better") for traditional video streaming.
* **AI Workshop:** SVTA will host an engineer-to-engineer workshop and hackathon on "AI in Media Distribution" in Rennes, France, in October 2024.

