### 5. Charter Review & Milestones
* **Presenter:** Leslie Daigle
* **Slides:** [MOPS Chair slides](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-mops-mops-chair-slides-00)

Leslie Daigle introduced a proposal to update the MOPS charter.
* **Proposed Change:** After seven years of successful operation and publishing three RFCs, the chairs propose removing the historical sentence: *"The IESG is establishing this working group on an experimental basis..."* to transition MOPS to a permanent operational working group.
* **AD Feedback:** Éric Vyncke (Internet AD) strongly supported the change, noting that the MOPS model has been highly successful and was used as a blueprint for other operational groups like IoT OPS and SRv6 OPS.
* **Milestones:** Tim Chown suggested adding new milestones, noting the last archived milestone was from 2022. Éric Vyncke responded that while the core charter text requires a formal IETF last call, milestones are indicative and can be updated flexibly by the chairs and AD.

